  m_text: 'Step-Up End User License Agreement (EULA)


    1. Acceptance of Terms

    By
    creating an account and using the Step-Up application, you acknowledge that you
    have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these terms. If you do not agree,
    do not use this application.


    2. Academic Project Disclaimer

    Step-Up
    is developed solely as an academic capstone simulation project. It is NOT a certified
    medical device, commercial fitness tracker, or professional health application.
    You use this application entirely at your own risk.


    3. Data Collection
    & GPS Tracking

    To function properly, Step-Up requires continuous access
    to your device''s pedometer (physical activity sensors) and background location
    (GPS) to track your physical movement and map your avatar to real-world coordinates.


    4.
    Data Storage & Privacy

    Your login credentials, step counts, and location
    history are transmitted to and stored securely on Firebase databases. We prioritize
    your privacy. This data will only be used for the evaluation of this academic
    project and will never be sold, rented, or distributed to third-party marketing
    agencies or advertisers.


    5. Physical Health Warning

    Always consult
    with a qualified healthcare provider before starting any new exercise program
    or strenuous fitness routine. If you experience faintness, dizziness, pain, or
    shortness of breath at any time while walking or using Step-Up, stop immediately.


    6.
    User Conduct

    Users agree to remain aware of their physical surroundings
    while using the application. Do not trespass on private property or enter dangerous
    areas (such as active roadways) to interact with the map.


    7. Account Termination

    The
    developers reserve the right to delete accounts, reset step counters, or terminate
    server access at any time without notice, particularly upon the completion of
    the academic evaluation period.


    Check the box below to acknowledge that
    you have read and accept these terms.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
